A4.text: Mount Kilimanjaro is the highest mountain in Africa and the highest free-standing mountain above sea level in the world

A5.text: Kilimanjaro's southern and eastern slopes served as the home of the Chagga Kingdoms until their abolition in 1963 by Julius Nyerere

A6.text: Mount Stanley is the fourth-highest mountain in Africa

A7.text: Mount Stanley is located in the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Uganda

A8.text: Mount Kenya is the second-highest peak in Africa, after Kilimanjaro
